    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-03T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-03T06:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7557</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-03T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1917, noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 4, 10
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1177. My 1175. Any promise of troops we might make would, of course, be
                    contingent on Italy’s fighting with all her might for herself. <persName
                        corresp="#p_PGJJ1">General Pershing</persName> can get exact situation from
                        <persName corresp="#p_RSW1">Generals Robertson</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_FGF1">Foch</persName>, who have been on the ground. I believe
                    Italian Government would rather have our declaration of war against Austria than
                    our troops.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
